Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper examines the growth and characteristics of a new OSN (Google+). 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper analyzes the behavior of users on a social media platform. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon privacy and security concerns related to using Google+. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper may discuss user experience and interface design on Google+. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon how information is shared and retrieved on Google+.
